thread.title: UNT sticking with McNulty at quarterback
thread.title_full: UNT sticking with McNulty at quarterback | Dallas Morning News

author: Brett Vito
title: UNT sticking with McNulty at quarterback
text:
DENTON - Senior Andrew McNulty will make his fifth straight start this season when UNT takes on Portland State in its homecoming game on Saturday.
McNulty has started each of UNT's first four games, but split time with DaMarcus Smith last week in a 49-14 loss to Southern Miss. McNulty threw for 131 yards and a touchdown on 11-of-21 passing, while Smith threw for 70 yards after connecting on 3-of-11 for 70 yards with an interception.
"Andrew McNulty is our starter," UNT coach Dan McCarney said. "I was really disappointed in the consistency of DaMarcus Smith when we did give him an opportunity. He does have talent, but the attention to detail is something he needs to make major, major improvement on. If he does then he has a chance to contend for the top spot. If he doesn't, we will get what we saw the other night."
McCarney said UNT has no plans to play Smith this week.
Briefly: Middle linebacker Blake Bean is expected to return to UNT's lineup Saturday after missing two games with a shoulder injury. Bean has 22 tackles on the season.
